## 2026-07-20

### Observation 1: Recognize pre-approved autonomous specifications

**Status:** ACTIONED (2026-07-20) — Applied to brainstorming (weekly review)
**Date:** 2026-07-20
**Session context:** Implementing one ordered task from an existing approved specification in an unattended loop.
**Skill:** brainstorming
**Type:** open-source
**Phase/Area:** Approval gate and transition to implementation

**Issue:** The skill requires fresh questions, a duplicate design document, a commit, and another user approval even when the user has already approved an exact repository specification and explicitly instructed the agent to proceed autonomously without pausing.

**Suggested improvement:** Add a preflight branch that recognizes an explicit implementation request against an existing accepted design as approval. Require a brief scope and test-seam summary, then transition directly to the existing plan while preserving any user prohibition on commits.

**Principle:** Workflow gates should recognize equivalent evidence already supplied by the user so they preserve intent without duplicating approval rituals.
